def to_float (s) :
   return float(s.replace(',','.'))

float_udf = udf(to_float , FloatType())

import seaborn as sns
def plot_bar(data1):    
    data1['Agriculture_USD'] = data1['Agriculture'] * data1['GDP ($ per capita)']
    data1['Industry_USD'] = data1['Industry'] * data1['GDP ($ per capita)']
    data1['Service_USD'] = data1['Service'] * data1['GDP ($ per capita)']
    
    data1[['Country', 'Agriculture_USD', 'Industry_USD', 'Service_USD']].set_index('Country').plot.bar(
        stacked=True, figsize=(14,7)
    )
    plt.ylabel('GDP ($ per capita)')
    plt.show()
data_poorest = data_poorest.toPandas()
plot_bar(data_poorest)

from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType
feet_to_m = udf(lambda x: x * 0.3048, DoubleType())
In [22]:
from pyspark.sql import functions as F
country_stats = (
    airports
    .groupBy("Country")
    .agg(
        F.count("Name").alias("Airport_Count"),
        F.max("Altitude").alias("Highest_Airport_ft"),
        F.min("Altitude").alias("Lowest_Airport_ft")
    )
    .where(F.col("Airport_Count") > 10)
    .withColumn("Highest_Airport_m", feet_to_m(F.col("Highest_Airport_ft")))
    .withColumn("Lowest_Airport_m", feet_to_m(F.col("Lowest_Airport_ft")))
    .withColumn("Diff", F.col("Highest_Airport_m") - F.col("Lowest_Airport_m"))
)
data3 = country_stats.orderBy(F.col("Diff")).limit(10)
data3.toPandas()

In [26]:
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType
import re

def fix_country(s):
    s = s.replace(", The", "") \
        .replace("Rep.", "Republic") \
        .replace("Korea, North", "North Korea") \
        .replace("Korea, South", "South Korea") \
        .replace("Is.", "Island") \
        .replace("&", "and") \
        .replace("Burma", "Myanmar") 
    
    s = re.sub("Congo.*", "Congo", s) 
    s = re.sub("Micronesia.*", "Micronesia", s) 
    
    return s

fix_country_udf = udf(
    lambda s: fix_country(s),
    StringType()
)
In [27]:
data_countries = (
    countries
    .withColumnRenamed("Area (sq. mi.)", "Area")
    .select("Country", "Area")
    .withColumn("Country", F.trim(F.col("Country")))
    .withColumn("Country", fix_country_udf("Country"))
)

data_airports = (
    airports
    .select("Country")
    .withColumn("Country", F.trim(F.col("Country")))
    .withColumn("Country", fix_country_udf("Country"))
)

countries_airports = (
    data_countries
    .join(data_airports, on="Country", how="left")
    .groupBy("Country", "Area")
    .agg(F.count("Country").alias("Count"))
    .drop("Country")
    .orderBy("Area")
)

countries_airports.toPandas().plot.scatter(
    x="Area",
    y="Count"
)
plt.show()

def region_to_continent(s):
    continents = {
        "BALTICS": "Europe",
        "IND. STATES": "Asia",
        "ASIA": "Asia",
        "EUROPE": "Europe",
        "NORTHERN AMERICA": "North America",
        "NEAR EAST": "Africa",
        "AFRICA": "Africa",
        "OCEANIA": "Australia/Oceania",
        "LATIN AMER": "South America"
    }
    
    for key, val in continents.items():
            if key in s:
                return val
    return None

region_to_continent_udf = udf(
    lambda s: region_to_continent(s),
    StringType()
)
